New Years Resolution! This is not a sponsored post, but a recommendation to read the Bible through in 2023 because it’s awesome. The BibleProject, which I love, has several “read through the Bible” plans on the Bible app. Their accompanying videos explaining the books and themes you’ll be encountering and they are fantastic. I also discovered a translation a few years ago called God’s Word that makes the read through super fun. I have a system of highlighting verses while reading, the basics are this: yellow = “theological content, PAY ATTENTION”, green = “humorous”, and purple = “weirdest/craziest/ I don’t even…”, like the dude with six fingers and toes definitely gets purple. My Old Testament has A LOT of green and purple. Scripture is alive and potent and hilarious and it will change you! From page one the Bible is a unified story that leads to Jesus. I challenge you to read it through this year. 1. Download the Bible app. 2. Get on that God’s Word translation. 3. Pick your highlighter colors. And, 4. hit up one of the Bible Project’s read the Bible in a year plans! Let’s Go!!!
We've got this, friends. 👊🏼

GO TELL IT ON THE MOUNTAIN — @crowder and I have this inside joke about me always asking him to scream a high B flat. When we recorded the track for the album in 2020, we were literally doing it over FaceTime. I threw him this idea, “Hey, what if you just scream this note?” and he’s like, “That’s super high, man, you sure about that?” But he gave it a shot and it turned out amazing in a way that only Crowder could deliver it. Crowder isn’t just a voice, he’s an entire vibe. I’m struggling to find the right words here, but he’s like this whole entity on his own. He has this unique style and energy that’s just so... Crowder. So when I was arranging this dark, hip-hop take on the song, Crowder’s voice just kept echoing in my head. It was clear that it had to be him on this track or it wouldn’t feel right. 

Then, for the live show, I asked him to yell that high Bb again... He just laughed and said he wasn’t sure what was going to come out but that he’d go for it. But man he nailed it! Sharing the stage with him for this was just epic.

Head over to the link in my bio to watch/listen to the full version of ‘Go Tell It On The Mountain’.
